title.narrative: 2.3: NUTRITION, POLICIES AND CAPACITIES

description.narrative: Output 2.3: NUTRITION By 2022, Nutrition national policies and institutional capacities are strengthened, which contributes to Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Nutrition In Early Childhood, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Safe And Equitable Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Services And Practices, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid), Water, Sanitation And Hygiene Systems And Empowerment Of Communities. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Survival and early developmentBy 2022, more vulnerable children in their early years (aged 0 to 6) have improved survival and are nurtured and stimulated for improved early childhood development.

title.narrative: Output 2.3: NUTRITION By 2022, Nutrition national policies and institutional capacities are strengthened

description.narrative: The National Food and Nutrition Strategy;2022-2030 was developed with strong support;and coordination;from;UNICEF. As a result of UNICEF’s;advocacy and technical support, the Ministry of Health and Population increased budget allocations for micronutrient supplementation for mothers and children. Innovative;training packages on detection and management of malnutrition and nutrition counseling, were delivered to 840;health workers. 505,204caregivers of children aged 6-23 months received IYCF counselling via face-to-face counselling and social;media platforms, while398,816childrenin 360 primary schoolshave improved knowledge on nutrition after attending nutrition awareness sessions delivered by trained personnel from the Water and Wastewater Holding Company.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/01/2022
